From 1935cff067fe573deebf5c65360513c0279359f9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 08:28:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Razorpay test-mode payment gateway to checkout

- New BackEnd/Controllers/PaymentController.js: creates a Razorpay order for
  the cart total (POST /api/payments/create-order) and independently
  verifies the HMAC-SHA256 payment signature Razorpay returns after
  checkout (POST /api/payments/verify, plus re-verified server-side in
  OrderController before any order is persisted - never trusts a
  client-supplied 'paid' flag on its own).
- BackEnd/Models/OrderModel.js: added paymentStatus ('cod'|'paid'|'failed'),
  paymentId, razorpayOrderId columns.
- BackEnd/Controllers/OrderController.js: when RAZORPAY_ENABLED=true,
  createOrder now requires and re-verifies a valid Razorpay signature
  before writing the order; falls back to the old COD behavior unchanged
  if the gateway is disabled/unset, so nothing breaks if env vars aren't
  configured yet.
- BackEnd/Routes/PaymentRoutes.js + Server.js: mounted at /api/payments,
  requireAuth + requireRole('user').
- BackEnd/package.json: added razorpay SDK dependency.
- BackEnd/.env.example: documented the 4 required env vars
  (RAZORPAY_KEY_ID/KEY_SECRET/MODE/ENABLED).
- project/src/lib/razorpay.ts: loads checkout.js on demand, wraps Razorpay
  Checkout in a promise-based openRazorpayCheckout() helper.
- project/src/pages/Cart.tsx: checkout flow is now create Razorpay order ->
  open Checkout -> place order with the payment proof attached. Button
  reads 'Pay & Place Order' and shows payment/placing stages while busy.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, vite build succeeds, backend files
node --check clean, and the signature-verification logic round-tripped
against a locally-computed HMAC using the real test key secret (accepts
valid signatures, rejects tampered/missing ones).
